<h2>Forums - Watches</h2>

Forum watches allow you to be notified when new posts arrive at the forum.
Watches can be set on either specific discussion threads, or on entire forums.
Watches can be configured to notify you when you view the forum, or you can
be notified via email.<br>
<br>
To add a topic to your watch list, click on the <b>Watch This Topic</b> link at
the top of the topic page or <b>Watch Forum</b> link at the top of the forum page. 
Click on the <b>Stop Watching</b> link to delete the watch. After 90 days, inactive
watches automatically expire.<br>
<br>
When in the Pente.org Forums, click the <b>My Watches</b> link to manage the watches
you currently have.  In <b>My Watches</b> you can choose to receive email notifications
when new posts are made, delete watches and stop watches from expiring.
To have a watch notify you by email, click in the <b>Email Updates</b> check box for
the watch you want to be notified about and then click <b>Update Watches</b>. Note that
updates will be mailed to the email address you registered with at Pente.org, you may
update your email address at My Profile.
To have a watch not expire, click in the <b>Save</b> check box for the watch you want to
save and then click <b>Update Watches</b>.
To delete a watch and stop notifications, click in the <b>Delete</b> check box for the
watch you want to delete and then click <b>Update Watches</b>.<br>
<br>
When in the Pente.org Forums, click the <b>My Settings</b> link to configure additional
watch settings such as automatically watching topics that you create or reply to,
and always notifying by email when watching topics.<br>
